00:15:44.340 --> 00:15:47.340
We definitely wanted to make ourselves available.

00:15:47.340 --> 00:15:51.340
What were you doing then if you weren't regular pioneering at that point?

00:15:51.340 --> 00:15:54.340
We both had a full-time jobs.

00:15:54.340 --> 00:16:00.340
And we were comfortable and enjoyed both of our jobs,

00:16:00.340 --> 00:16:01.340
secular jobs.

00:16:01.340 --> 00:16:04.340
So the idea of regular pioneering was there.

00:16:04.340 --> 00:16:07.340
Like I said, it was a goal that I previously had.

00:16:07.340 --> 00:16:09.340
But we had a long way to go.

00:16:09.340 --> 00:16:11.340
Now, you had mentioned to me earlier

00:16:11.340 --> 00:16:14.340
that you were about 16 years older.

00:16:14.340 --> 00:16:16.340
So when you first had this goal to pioneer.

00:16:16.340 --> 00:16:17.340
Yes.

00:16:17.340 --> 00:16:19.340
From 16 to what point do you finally now

00:16:19.340 --> 00:16:22.340
reach entering the pioneer service?

00:16:22.340 --> 00:16:24.340
Yes. So we started.

00:16:24.340 --> 00:16:27.340
I was in my late 20s when we started.

00:16:27.340 --> 00:16:29.340
I was in my mid 30s when I started.

00:16:29.340 --> 00:16:31.340
We wanted to, like we said before,

00:16:31.340 --> 00:16:33.340
we wanted to increase our service to Jehovah.

00:16:34.340 --> 00:16:36.340
But there were different challenges there.

00:16:36.340 --> 00:16:38.340
It's different adjustment that we wanted to do.

00:16:38.340 --> 00:16:41.340
And something a turning point that happened at that time.

00:16:41.340 --> 00:16:44.340
When we wanted to expand our ministry service

00:16:44.340 --> 00:16:47.340
to be more useful in the hands of Jehovah.

00:16:47.340 --> 00:16:49.340
The street could overheat of that time.

00:16:49.340 --> 00:16:53.340
It was brother Jean Papino, his wife, sister Carla Papino.

00:16:53.340 --> 00:16:57.340
They encouraged us very much to take the regular pioneering.

00:16:57.340 --> 00:16:58.340
Yes.

00:16:58.340 --> 00:17:01.340
I remember being with them out in the ministry during the week

00:17:01.340 --> 00:17:03.340
that they would come to the congregation.

00:17:03.340 --> 00:17:06.339
And we always make a stop and go for coffee.

00:17:06.339 --> 00:17:10.339
And we would enjoy their experiences and just that happiness

00:17:10.339 --> 00:17:14.339
that we would see in them after each visit as a family worship.

00:17:14.339 --> 00:17:19.339
We would discuss and see how we could then simplify our lives.

00:17:19.339 --> 00:17:20.339
Because that was it.

00:17:20.339 --> 00:17:22.339
We needed to simplify our lives.

00:17:22.339 --> 00:17:26.339
And we started by taking regularly the auxiliary pioneer.

00:17:26.339 --> 00:17:30.339
And we became then eventually we started both

00:17:30.339 --> 00:17:32.339
this new chapter of our lives.

00:17:32.339 --> 00:17:34.339
We became regular pioneers.

00:17:34.339 --> 00:17:37.339
Now you're in your early to mid 30s.

00:17:37.339 --> 00:17:38.339
You're in your late 20s.

00:17:38.339 --> 00:17:40.339
And now you're with that encouragement.

00:17:40.339 --> 00:17:43.339
You're entering the pioneer service. That's good.

00:17:43.339 --> 00:17:46.339
So the pioneering, what you started pioneering is

00:17:46.339 --> 00:17:48.339
is that what now stirred your desire

00:17:48.339 --> 00:17:50.339
to want to serve with the need was greater?

00:17:50.339 --> 00:17:53.339
Oh, no, not at all.

00:17:53.339 --> 00:17:57.339
We always thought that serving in another country

00:17:57.339 --> 00:18:01.339
or with the need is greater even where the country we were

00:18:01.339 --> 00:18:04.339
was some maybe an experience from the yearbook,

00:18:04.339 --> 00:18:05.339
but not for us.

00:18:05.339 --> 00:18:08.339
And we thought that we just had waited too long,

00:18:08.339 --> 00:18:10.339
probably to take those type of decisions.

00:18:10.339 --> 00:18:14.339
So it was not something that we thought we could do.

00:18:14.339 --> 00:18:16.339
Correct. That's it.

00:18:16.339 --> 00:18:19.339
Many times we thought that we have waited too long

00:18:19.339 --> 00:18:21.339
to start regular pioneering.

00:18:21.339 --> 00:18:24.339
So the idea of serving in another country

00:18:24.339 --> 00:18:26.339
was never came to our mind.

00:18:26.339 --> 00:18:29.339
However, another turning point in our life

00:18:29.339 --> 00:18:33.339
was the encouragement of brother Jean Papino

00:18:33.339 --> 00:18:34.339
and his wife.

00:18:34.339 --> 00:18:37.339
Now you mentioned to me earlier that

00:18:37.339 --> 00:18:41.339
Brother Papino gave you an illustration

00:18:41.339 --> 00:18:44.339
that really got you thinking.

00:18:44.339 --> 00:18:45.339
What was that?

00:18:45.339 --> 00:18:50.339
Yes. When we were deciding to move,

00:18:50.339 --> 00:18:52.339
there was always fears.

00:18:53.339 --> 00:18:54.339
It's certain fears.

00:18:54.339 --> 00:18:57.339
Despite the fact that we were kind of already

00:18:57.339 --> 00:18:58.339
have the decision to go.

00:18:58.339 --> 00:19:01.339
So I mentioned this to Brother Papino

00:19:01.339 --> 00:19:03.339
about the fears we have.

00:19:03.339 --> 00:19:05.339
So he gave me an illustration.

00:19:05.339 --> 00:19:08.339
He told me, imagine there is a father

00:19:08.339 --> 00:19:11.339
and in front of him is a table.

00:19:11.339 --> 00:19:14.339
And on top of the table is his baby child

00:19:14.339 --> 00:19:16.339
of a two-year-old.

00:19:16.339 --> 00:19:18.339
And then all of a sudden,

00:19:18.339 --> 00:19:21.339
imagine that the child jumps to the floor

00:19:21.339 --> 00:19:22.339
and he asks me,

00:19:22.339 --> 00:19:24.339
what do you think the father is going to do?

00:19:24.339 --> 00:19:26.339
And I say, wow, he's going to write

00:19:26.339 --> 00:19:28.339
or we're going to try to grab his baby

00:19:28.339 --> 00:19:30.339
to a boy he stays on the floor.

00:19:30.339 --> 00:19:32.339
And he told me, well, that's exactly

00:19:32.339 --> 00:19:33.339
what you hope is going to do.

00:19:33.339 --> 00:19:34.339
If you jump to Peru,

00:19:34.339 --> 00:19:36.339
if you step over to Peru.

00:19:36.339 --> 00:19:38.339
So that was beautiful.

00:19:38.339 --> 00:19:41.339
And that gave us the strength,

00:19:41.339 --> 00:19:44.339
we can say, to achieve

00:19:44.339 --> 00:19:47.339
and take the decision to move to Peru.

00:19:47.339 --> 00:19:49.339
So what an illustration

00:19:49.339 --> 00:19:52.339
to get your minds and hearts thinking on it.

00:19:52.339 --> 00:19:54.339
Like he said, there was many fears.

00:19:54.339 --> 00:19:57.339
And also, we had our lives in Canada,

00:19:57.339 --> 00:19:58.339
our families.

00:19:58.339 --> 00:20:00.339
We had never been away from our families.

00:20:00.339 --> 00:20:02.339
But the encouragement we received

00:20:02.339 --> 00:20:04.339
definitely made a good impression.

00:20:04.339 --> 00:20:06.339
And then we prayed about it.

00:20:06.339 --> 00:20:10.339
And yes, we thought that it was possible for us.

00:20:10.339 --> 00:20:12.339
But it was not easy.

00:20:12.339 --> 00:20:14.339
We still wanted to do certain,

00:20:14.339 --> 00:20:17.339
needed to do certain adjustments.

00:20:17.339 --> 00:20:20.339
So Brother Papino was always encouraging us.

00:20:20.339 --> 00:20:24.339
Yes, he said, just to try it one year or two.

00:20:24.339 --> 00:20:25.339
Just to try it.

00:20:25.339 --> 00:20:27.339
If something doesn't work,

00:20:27.339 --> 00:20:29.339
then you can always come back.

00:20:29.339 --> 00:20:31.339
But you can taste what it is.

00:20:31.339 --> 00:20:33.339
What difference did that make for you?

00:20:33.339 --> 00:20:35.339
For him to give you that encouragement,

00:20:35.339 --> 00:20:38.339
to just put it in the context of just a year or two.

00:20:38.339 --> 00:20:40.339
Did that affect your decision at all?

00:20:40.339 --> 00:20:42.339
You know, way yes.

00:20:42.339 --> 00:20:45.339
Because, you know, the idea of moving,

00:20:45.339 --> 00:20:47.339
it was a big change.

00:20:47.339 --> 00:20:49.339
It was a big decision for us.

00:20:49.339 --> 00:20:52.339
And having in mind that we could go for one year,

00:20:52.339 --> 00:20:54.339
try it out, and then come back,

00:20:54.339 --> 00:20:58.339
it kind of smoothed the fears.

00:20:58.339 --> 00:21:01.339
So that was a good example for us.

00:21:01.339 --> 00:21:04.339
And we took the decision to move.

00:21:04.339 --> 00:21:06.339
We make certain adjustments in our life,

00:21:06.339 --> 00:21:09.339
in our secular works.

00:21:09.339 --> 00:21:11.339
We sell our belongings.

00:21:11.339 --> 00:21:13.339
And we set up a date.

00:21:13.339 --> 00:21:16.339
We had a date and said, by the end of this year,

00:21:16.339 --> 00:21:19.339
that was in 2012, we need to go to Peru.

00:21:19.339 --> 00:21:20.339
Yes.

00:21:20.339 --> 00:21:21.339
So you get down there.

00:21:21.339 --> 00:21:23.339
Where do you go once you arrive there?

00:21:23.339 --> 00:21:25.339
We arrive to Lima.

00:21:25.339 --> 00:21:27.339
And just a few weeks after,

00:21:27.339 --> 00:21:29.339
we move to Takna.

00:21:29.339 --> 00:21:32.339
This is the city in the south of Peru,

00:21:32.339 --> 00:21:33.339
border with Chile.

00:21:33.339 --> 00:21:36.339
We took a bus from Lima to Takna.

00:21:36.339 --> 00:21:40.339
That's 22 hours travel, a trip of 22 hours.

00:21:41.339 --> 00:21:43.339
So the south of Peru is desert.

00:21:43.339 --> 00:21:44.339
So you could imagine.

00:21:44.339 --> 00:21:47.339
So after five hours, six hours, seven hours, ten hours.

00:21:47.339 --> 00:21:48.339
I saw it on my left.

00:21:48.339 --> 00:21:49.339
It was sand.

00:21:49.339 --> 00:21:50.339
My ride was sand.

00:21:50.339 --> 00:21:51.339
On the back was sand.

00:21:51.339 --> 00:21:52.339
In the front was sand.

00:21:52.339 --> 00:21:54.339
So I said, Sandrina, where are we going?

00:21:54.339 --> 00:21:55.339
No idea.

00:21:55.339 --> 00:21:58.339
It was like that at all.

00:21:58.339 --> 00:22:01.339
But eventually, after 22 hours,

00:22:01.339 --> 00:22:03.339
we could see the city.

00:22:03.339 --> 00:22:04.339
We arrived.

00:22:04.339 --> 00:22:06.339
And yes, we were not going to leave just on sand.

00:22:06.339 --> 00:22:08.339
There was actually a city there.

00:22:08.339 --> 00:22:10.339
And that was going to be our new home.

00:22:10.339 --> 00:22:12.339
It started since the beginning of the first day.

00:22:12.339 --> 00:22:15.339
Jehovah was proving us that he was going to be there with us.

00:22:15.339 --> 00:22:19.339
And then another door opened for us.

00:22:19.339 --> 00:22:22.339
And that was to apply for the Biblical school

00:22:22.339 --> 00:22:25.339
for Christian couples back then.

00:22:25.339 --> 00:22:27.339
So when that door opened,

00:22:27.339 --> 00:22:32.339
we knew that the idea of just one year or two in Peru

00:22:32.339 --> 00:22:34.339
was going to change.

00:22:34.339 --> 00:22:35.339
And that's what happened.

00:22:35.339 --> 00:22:37.339
We attended school.

00:22:37.339 --> 00:22:40.339
One year and a half after we arrived in Tacna,

00:22:40.339 --> 00:22:42.339
that's when we were invited.

00:22:42.339 --> 00:22:45.339
And then we received an assignment.

00:22:45.339 --> 00:22:46.339
Yes.

00:22:46.339 --> 00:22:50.339
They give us the assignment to serve as temporary special pioneers

00:22:50.339 --> 00:22:54.339
in Abancai, which is in the Andes area of Peru.

00:22:54.339 --> 00:22:56.339
So you went from the desert to the mountains?

00:22:56.339 --> 00:22:57.339
Yes.

00:22:57.339 --> 00:23:01.339
So how long were you there in your special pioneer assignment?

00:23:01.339 --> 00:23:04.339
It was in total maybe five months.

00:23:04.339 --> 00:23:05.339
Yes.

00:23:05.339 --> 00:23:06.339
Why so short?

00:23:06.339 --> 00:23:08.339
The branch office calls us again,

00:23:08.339 --> 00:23:11.339
telling us that now we were going to receive an order assignment

00:23:11.339 --> 00:23:14.339
to work in the circuit work, serving the circuit work.

00:23:14.339 --> 00:23:17.339
But the circuit work was going to be in Lima.

00:23:17.339 --> 00:23:22.339
So you still had yet another course adjustment ahead of you.

00:23:22.339 --> 00:23:25.339
How long were you there in the circuit work now in Lima?

00:23:25.339 --> 00:23:29.339
So around the two years serving in that circuit work,

00:23:29.339 --> 00:23:31.339
in that circuit,

00:23:31.339 --> 00:23:33.339
the branch office called me.

00:23:33.339 --> 00:23:38.339
And the brother told me that they wanted to see us at the branch

00:23:38.339 --> 00:23:40.339
next Monday.

00:23:40.339 --> 00:23:42.339
So he said, fine, we can go there.

00:23:42.339 --> 00:23:44.339
We can be there at next Monday at 8 a.m.

00:23:44.339 --> 00:23:47.339
And he said, just make sure to bring your things

00:23:47.339 --> 00:23:49.339
to stay two weeks with us.

00:23:49.339 --> 00:23:50.339
Two weeks.

00:23:50.339 --> 00:23:53.339
What was going through your mind when they told you that?

00:23:53.339 --> 00:23:55.339
We actually had no idea.

00:23:55.339 --> 00:23:57.339
They told us a training.

00:23:57.339 --> 00:23:59.339
So we went for two weeks.

00:23:59.339 --> 00:24:00.339
Yes.

00:24:00.339 --> 00:24:03.339
And then at the end of the two weeks,

00:24:03.339 --> 00:24:06.339
they told us the extended for two a month.

00:24:06.339 --> 00:24:09.339
After one month, they extended two months.

00:24:09.339 --> 00:24:12.339
After two months, they extended six months.

00:24:12.339 --> 00:24:16.339
And then when all this happened, I said, wait a minute.

00:24:16.339 --> 00:24:19.339
Two weeks, one month, two months, six months.

00:24:19.339 --> 00:24:23.339
Am I entering Bethel at my mid-40s?

00:24:23.339 --> 00:24:24.339
Yes.

00:24:24.339 --> 00:24:25.339
So it was surprising for us.

00:24:25.339 --> 00:24:26.339
Yes.

00:24:26.339 --> 00:24:28.339
And after six months, maybe I can say that.

00:24:28.339 --> 00:24:31.339
Yes, after six months, we received a letter

00:24:31.339 --> 00:24:34.339
that was our new assignment.

00:24:34.339 --> 00:24:36.339
And we could not believe it.

00:24:36.339 --> 00:24:40.339
I mean, like he said, we had passed that age or reached that age

00:24:40.339 --> 00:24:44.339
where normally you don't start serving at Bethel.

00:24:44.339 --> 00:24:47.339
It's so how long have you been there in the Bethel and Peru?

00:24:47.339 --> 00:24:48.339
It's been six years.

00:24:48.339 --> 00:24:49.339
Six years.

00:24:49.339 --> 00:24:50.339
Yes.

00:24:50.339 --> 00:24:54.339
So how many years then has it been since you left Montreal?

00:24:54.339 --> 00:24:55.339
Almost 10 years.

00:24:55.339 --> 00:24:56.339
10 years.

00:24:56.339 --> 00:24:59.339
Do you think, Brother Papino knew what he was doing when he told you

00:24:59.339 --> 00:25:01.339
to just try it for a year, too?

00:25:01.339 --> 00:25:07.339
He definitely knew the blessings that we were going to enjoy in Peru.

00:25:07.339 --> 00:25:11.339
And I think the best counsel he gave us just to give it a try

00:25:11.339 --> 00:25:15.339
for one year and see how it goes was the best.

00:25:15.339 --> 00:25:18.339
And a whole decade has passed since then.

00:25:18.339 --> 00:25:23.339
When you look back over those life course adjustments,

00:25:23.339 --> 00:25:26.339
